# <type>[module]: <subject>
#
# Body (optional)
# 
# Footer (optional)
#

# --- COMMIT TYPE ---
# feat[module]:     A new feature
# fix[module]:      A bug fix
# docs[module]:     Documentation only changes
# style[module]:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
# refactor[module]: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# perf[module]:     A code change that improves performance
# test[module]:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
# chore[module]:    Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools
#
# --- MODULE EXAMPLES ---
# PID, LQR, KF, Plant, Main, Build, Docs
#
# --- SUBJECT RULES ---
# - Use imperative, present tense: "add" not "added" nor "adds"
# - Don't capitalize first letter
# - No period (.) at the end
# - Keep it short and descriptive
#
# --- BODY RULES (optional) ---
# - Separate subject from body with a blank line
# - Wrap at 72 characters
# - Use body to explain what and why vs. how
#
# --- EXAMPLES ---
# feat[PID]: add incremental PID controller for circular trajectory tracking
# fix[KF]: correct state transition matrix dimension mismatch
# refactor[Plant]: simplify dynamics model initialization
# docs[Main]: update README with build instructions
#
# --- FULL EXAMPLE ---
# feat[PID]: implement anti-windup mechanism
#
# Add saturation limits to prevent integral windup in PID controller.
# This improves stability when the system reaches physical constraints.
#
# Closes #123
